function isPrime(n) {
  if (n < 2) return false;
  if (n === 2) return true;
  if (n % 2 === 0) return false;
  for (let i = 3; i <= Math.sqrt(n); i += 2) {
    if (n % i === 0) return false;
  }
  return true;
}
```

**How it works:**
- Returns `false` for numbers < 2
- Handles 2 (only even prime) as a special case
- Skips even numbers, then checks odd divisors up to √n — O(√n) time complexity

**Usage:**
